Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.92,0:00:02.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Victory! Honesty! The shocking evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.85,0:00:04.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The inexhaustible drive to aim for the top!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.64,0:00:06.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We forge ahead towards the solution!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.27,0:00:07.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both the case and their love have a surprising development!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.90,0:00:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can Detective Takagi decide it today for sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.77,0:00:11.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.28,0:00:12.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body of a child and the brains of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.94,0:00:14.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.34,0:01:47.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By coincidence we bumped into Detective Takagi and others who were attending a singles party.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.71,0:01:54.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, sometime during the singles party, a cousin of one of the attendees, Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, was kidnapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.92,0:01:59.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit's demand was for one million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.04,0:01:59.24,Signs,,0,0,0,,I got the boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.04,0:01:59.24,Signs,,0,0,0,,Prepare 1 million Yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.04,0:01:59.24,Signs,,0,0,0,,I will contact you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.04,0:01:59.24,Signs,,0,0,0,,Tell to the Police, I will kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.89,0:02:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Metropolitan Police Detective Love Story 7 (Part 2)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.47,0:02:10.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm, so the ransom condition is 1 million yen?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.23,0:02:12.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's aismall sum compared to the usual outrageous amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.31,0:02:19.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, since the culprit seems to know Masashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, he's probably taking his real financial situation into consideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.03,0:02:23.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, I understand. In the meantime, I'll have investigators stakeout those three people's homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.41,0:02:28.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} saw a live broadcast of a baseball game on March 26th.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.25,0:02:31.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According the season, it was either a high school baseball invitational or a pre-season professional game.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.42,0:02:39.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said it was a boring game, so if we can find out which game it was, we might determine the culprit from the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.42,0:02:41.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir. Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.43,0:02:43.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I found something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.01,0:02:47.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There wasn't a pre-season professional game on that day, but..
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.39,0:02:49.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were three high school games.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.18,0:02:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So; which of those was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.60,0:02:54.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well.. the first game was 7 to 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.52,0:02:57.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was reversal after reversal, so it was a very close game.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.82,0:03:02.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It went to the 12th inning, lasting from10:00 until 2:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.41,0:03:05.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm, can't imagine that one being boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.53,0:03:07.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think so either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.20,0:03:10.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, the second one ended at 4:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.29,0:03:15.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The result was 14 to 5. One team kept pounding away and scored a crushing victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.71,0:03:19.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it that one? Sounds like a one-sided and boring game.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.34,0:03:23.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, but the losing school had a player who's gotten the attention of the professional leagues...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.80,0:03:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He hit 6 out of 6, including 2 home runs Quite an effort, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.93,0:03:28.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the last one?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.62,0:03:30.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it was 1 to 2 pitchers' battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.35,0:03:36.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both of them got out of a pinch multiple times, The win was from a walk-off home run in the bottom of the 9th.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.11,0:03:39.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It ended precisely at 7:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.07,0:03:42.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That game would have been pretty interesting too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.53,0:03:46.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, maybe he saw a regular TV program?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.32,0:03:48.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They might have shown baseball on one of those top.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.91,0:03:52.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, like on cable TV or satellite or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.50,0:03:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.62,0:04:00.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see, shown on satellite from 12:00 to 1:00, "Major League Digest" (Nice Game Selection)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.38,0:04:06.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From 3:00 to 5:00 was "Falcon's: The Track to Victory," a rebroadcast of last year's special on Nichiuri TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.51,0:04:12.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and on Cable TV, from 6:00 to 7:00 pm, there was a special show about the player, Kiyomatsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.64,0:04:16.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm, there's no way the "Nice Game Selection" would be boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.31,0:04:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And "The Track to Victory" sounds like it should be interesting as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.23,0:04:23.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, could it have been the special about Kiyomatsu?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.53,0:04:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, mom said she saw it She said they showed all of Kiyomatsu's home runs since his debut and it was really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.00,0:04:37.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, instead... A video! Maybe a baseball video was playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.83,0:04:39.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think that's the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.50,0:04:43.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouta said, he turn the TV himself with the remote.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.50,0:04:43.26,Signs,,0,0,0,,Emoto Aya (28)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.50,0:04:43.26,Signs,,0,0,0,,Illustrator
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.01,0:04:51.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, maybe anticipating that Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} would do that, the culprit setup an unrelated baseball video earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.10,0:04:52.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to confuse the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.02,0:04:54.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.31,0:04:56.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was using the remote, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.89,0:04:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he changed the channel he'd realize right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.40,0:05:00.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's right..
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.77,0:05:07.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, are you sure Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} didn't tell you what time he went to the man's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.57,0:05:11.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, it seems that somehow that man really convinced him not to speak about it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.91,0:05:16.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It took some time to finally get him to admit to receiving that card and going to that man's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.54,0:05:18.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.54,0:05:21.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} received a rare Kamen Yaiba card...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.92,0:05:26.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then isn't the guy who collects them, that modeler Hikiya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the suspicious one?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.77,0:05:26.12,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hikiya Kadonari (25)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.77,0:05:26.12,Signs,,0,0,0,,Modeler
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.84,0:05:32.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, even though I said it was rare, they sell things like that for around 3000 yen at shops.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.84,0:05:32.30,Signs,,0,0,0,,Emoto Masashi (26)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.84,0:05:32.30,Signs,,0,0,0,,Sports Gym Trainer
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.60,0:05:35.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Any adult could have bought that card.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.73,0:05:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's nothing like the illusory 800,000 yen premium card we were both hoping for.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.23,0:05:47.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, back then Hikiya said he sentyou a pack of cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.95,0:05:51.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure that premium card wasn't inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.82,0:05:54.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you already. It wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.03,0:05:56.24,Signs,,0,0,0,,Satsuka Yoshikane (31)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.03,0:05:56.24,Signs,,0,0,0,,Paper Money Collector
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.03,0:05:59.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of premium, Satsuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said he sent 30 000 yen to you by registered mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.71,0:06:02.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could one with all the same numbers have been mixed in or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.79,0:06:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.88,0:06:07.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't take notice of the number on each and every bill I get.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.49,0:06:07.42,Signs,,0,0,0,,Musician
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.49,0:06:07.42,Signs,,0,0,0,,Rokuda Takuji (26)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.01,0:06:10.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, I'didn'teven check the lottery tickets Rokuda sent me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.80,0:06:12.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just not interested in that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.81,0:06:15.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, what about a movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.43,0:06:18.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could that baseball game have been a scene from a movie or drama?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.44,0:06:20.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.48,0:06:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you check on that possibility?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.81,0:06:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.61,0:06:24.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For movies and dramas...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.77,0:06:26.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all romances.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.22,0:06:27.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"My Wonderful Affair."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.53,0:06:31.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One about an aristocratic group date, "The Lovers Who Passed by Each Other."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.07,0:06:34.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One about lovers separating/ "The Too-Brief Spring"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.74,0:06:38.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh, ah, those really were the programs shown that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.87,0:06:41.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only went because of the food.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.04,0:06:44.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't know it was a singles party.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.96,0:06:46.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.92,0:06:48.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.51,0:06:51.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what's with those clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.47,0:06:53.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were you trying to show off?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.09,0:06:56.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could say the same for you, why would you be wearing make-up?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.47,0:06:59.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? This? Yumi forced me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.93,0:07:02.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same here! Chiba forced me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.10,0:07:05.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not that it matters anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.69,0:07:06.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.72,0:07:08.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't matter at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.90,0:07:11.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what're you guys doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.12,0:07:15.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.12,0:07:17.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Megure. How's it going there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.49,0:07:23.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for us, we haven't been able to find any game shown the day that looks boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.62,0:07:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey... Everyone's staking out those three people's homes now and waiting to break in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.42,0:07:32.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this drags on much longer, the boy's life could be in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.72,0:07:36.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.51,0:07:39.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouta!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.14,0:07:42.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.52,0:07:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You haven't be injured, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.19,0:07:45.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.23,0:07:50.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in the car of the man from before, but I got tired and fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.57,0:07:52.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy, where does he live?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.65,0:07:53.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's his apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.82,0:07:55.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Who's this lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.91,0:07:56.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's a police1 officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.99,0:07:58.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell me, Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.62,0:08:02.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I already promised that man I will never say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.12,0:08:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man kidnapped you, so he's a bad person
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.38,0:08:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.04,0:08:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.34,0:08:11.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all OK now, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.71,0:08:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he's home safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.34,0:08:15.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must have been one of my buddies.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.09,0:08:19.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some practical joke, though I admit it was in bad taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.59,0:08:21.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could this be a practical joke?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.06,0:08:23.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.18,0:08:24.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.73,0:08:29.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you see, the boy we thought had been kidnapped just came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.27,0:08:31.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!? Did you give the 1 million yen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.11,0:08:34.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the culprit hasn'teven contacted us yet
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.15,0:08:38.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} doesn't even intend to hand over the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.49,0:08:42.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, it's already late for today, Kouta.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.41,0:08:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well talk about this tomorrow, go on to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.16,0:08:45.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.38,0:08:55.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.84,0:09:00.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened to your socks? They look like they're wet
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.81,0:09:02.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.35,0:09:08.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remembered that Masashi-niichan said I mustn't take things from strange men.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.44,0:09:14.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So after saying bye-bye to the man with the beard, I went back to return the card he gave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.70,0:09:20.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then he wasn't in the apartment Instead there was a man I didn't know irTtrfe bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.41,0:09:22.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An unknown man in the bathroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.25,0:09:27.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, as for us, let's leave the rest to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.71,0:09:29.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's time for the sports news.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.92,0:09:32.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like to see the results of the World Cup preliminaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.63,0:09:34.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, do you mind if I use the TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.09,0:09:36.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no. Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.59,0:09:41.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so it's 0 to 0. A scoreless draw, but still a great game!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.97,0:09:43.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What, 0 to 0?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.02,0:09:46.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess that's not bad for an away game.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.73,0:09:48.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A scoreless draw?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.27,0:09:51.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, that's why Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.52,0:09:54.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person must be the culprit then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.50,0:10:11.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I already tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.29,0:10:15.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was just a stupid practical joke by one of my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.59,0:10:19.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably took Kouta just to see me freak out
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.72,0:10:22.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, Kouta came back safe and sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.80,0:10:23.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.10,0:10:26.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The kidnapper not only demanded one million yen...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.60,0:10:30.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He left a message saying he would kill Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} if you reported it to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.98,0:10:34.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was a clear threat, inexcusable for a practical joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.32,0:10:39.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus your voice was heard from the answering machine in the kidnapper's apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.28,0:10:43.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the culprit must be one of the three people you telephoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.99,0:10:45.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't just let this go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.91,0:10:50.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. Let's go together, and visit their houses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.71,0:10:55.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though the culprit was disguised at the time, if we go now, you'll know who's apartment it was, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.63,0:10:57.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, but..,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.13,0:10:59.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! I'm telling you that isn't necessary!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.97,0:11:04.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a sec. Since Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} has come back home, you must haveTalready paid the ransom money-
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.30,0:11:07.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I'd done that, the officers would definitely have noticed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.77,0:11:10.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you might have given something else to the culprit
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.52,0:11:14.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe there was something of value in the things they sent you ancl you returned it or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.02,0:11:17.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, didn't I just say-
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.11,0:11:18.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-re-re!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.28,0:11:20.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This picture was in Aya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-oneesan{\r}'s e-mail!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.95,0:11:23.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, what are you looking at!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.28,0:11:27.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! This? An illustrator friend of mine sends me these joke messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.08,0:11:30.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, will you stop it, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.54,0:11:34.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, you see, it said "Click This" on the e-mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.88,0:11:38.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I knew what was inside before I opened it, I wouldn't have done it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.96,0:11:44.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! First of all, you shouldn't open other people's mail no matter what the contents!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.47,0:11:44.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.51,0:11:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The kidnapper picked the time when both Masashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Aya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would be out at the singles party to break in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.89,0:11:52.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted to steal something, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.02,0:11:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, Hikiya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who sent the Yaiba cards is in the clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.61,0:12:01.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't go through all this trouble of this plan if he didn't know what was inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.49,0:12:02.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.57,0:12:05.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that respect, there are the lottery tickets that Rokuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} sent
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.57,0:12:11.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the winner was a number continuing from the tickets he had himself, then he would know the winning ticket.was'here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.45,0:12:12.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.41,0:12:14.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you could say the same thing for Satsuka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.83,0:12:17.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he'd lost one of the rare bills he'd bought..
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.92,0:12:21.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be strange for him to think he'd accidentally sent it to Masashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.38,0:12:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of sending things, didn't a bottle wrapped in shiny paper arrive for Uncle Kogoro the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.26,0:12:31.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that was champagne.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.14,0:12:35.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a thank you gift from one of dad's clients.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.56,0:12:38.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a kind of juice, right? I wanted to try some too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.23,0:12:40.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's alcohol, so children are not allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.15,0:12:43.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, Dad already drank it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.57,0:12:46.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess I couldn't then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.24,0:12:47.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, right
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.53,0:12:52.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it was alcohol, Uncle opened it up as soon as it arrived and put it in his stomach, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.45,0:12:53.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.83,0:12:59.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you receive money through registered mail, normally you put it in your wallet right away after you open it
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.21,0:13:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means if any rare bills had been mixed in, they'd be in Masashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s wallet
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.55,0:13:06.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if he broke into the house, he couldn't get his hands on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.97,0:13:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, the suspicious one...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.72,0:13:12.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is the one who sent the lottery tickets, Rokuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.27,0:13:14.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.18,0:13:18.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He knows don't care about lotteries and might have just thrown them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.04,0:13:24.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also knows it possible you might have left them unopened on the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.48,0:13:28.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you don't care about them, you might not notice if they were gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.95,0:13:32.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naturally you might not even realize that they had been stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.04,0:13:33.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on a moment
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.29,0:13:35.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you forgetting something?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.83,0:13:40.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouta said he watched a boring baseball game at that man's apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.63,0:13:44.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just past noon on that day when I called Rokuda's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.05,0:13:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,,The only two games on TV at that time was the close high school baseball game with reversal after reversal,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.51,0:13:53.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,AncTthe Major League "Nice Game Selection."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.31,0:13:57.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kouta. That game you saw was boring, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.39,0:13:59.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was no fun at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.27,0:14:03.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? Rokuda couldn't be the culprit
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.32,0:14:08.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, say, it says here that the "Nice Game , Selection" was an "anzenjiai" (safe game).
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.70,0:14:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was safe, then wouldn't it be dull and unexciting?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.99,0:14:13.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.91,0:14:18.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's read "kanzenjiai". It's what they call a ''perfect game".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.21,0:14:23.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's when the pitcher doesn't let the opposing batters score even one hit It's as exciting a game as you can get!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.46,0:14:24.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.34,0:14:28.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true'a perfect game can be thrilling.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.72,0:14:33.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But for a child not familiar with the details of baseball, it might seem like a game where nothing happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.55,0:14:36.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, if the broadcast window was only one hour long,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.56,0:14:43.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If could be almost cut to just that pitcher's plays, so it would only show scenes of the opposing batters getting out
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.40,0:14:45.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It makes sense that he would call it boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.53,0:14:48.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. Are we right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.28,0:14:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The batters kept getting three strikes, so everyone was just getting outs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.78,0:14:58.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this it's clear that the kidnapper was Rokuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.75,0:14:59.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-wait
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.29,0:15:03.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if Rokuda is the culprit, it was only an attempt, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.25,0:15:05.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like he got any money from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.29,0:15:09.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, it seems he's hard up fonmoney. I'm sure he just unconsciously gave into'temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.72,0:15:11.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew it, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.68,0:15:13.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That one of those lottery tickets was a winner.-
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.80,0:15:19.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew he was hard up for money, so you sent the tickets back to him still in the envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.35,0:15:23.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, not knowing that, Rokuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} snuck into this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.90,0:15:27.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lottery tickets weren't here and, in his impatience, he kidnapped Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.23,0:15:33.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, because of his situation, you suspected Rokuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.41,0:15:35.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you said we should go over to his apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.03,0:15:38.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you saw the mail still in there in his mailbox...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.45,0:15:44.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe there's something good in that bulging mailbox of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.54,0:15:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what you said, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.38,0:15:48.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did I get that wrong anywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.01,0:15:54.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's right It's just as you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.80,0:15:55.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's OK, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.51,0:15:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was the one who bought the lottery tickets originally.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.06,0:16:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, he's the only one. He never gave up music, even now he still doing it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.94,0:16:05.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was our dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.36,0:16:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our group from long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.61,0:16:11.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone became bitter and quit
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.28,0:16:13.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Except him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.36,0:16:17.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, please forgive him this time, Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.37,0:16:19.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.58,0:16:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kidnapping is a extremely vulgar crime, rigirt up there with murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.87,0:16:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't excuse it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.58,0:16:27.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially since it was just for money.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.46,0:16:31.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, a dream that needs to stab people in the heart to become true...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.88,0:16:35.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's hard to sympathize with someone holding on to something so unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.59,0:16:37.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's..
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.93,0:16:40.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That foolish guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.31,0:16:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, we're going to raid Rokuda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.31,0:16:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, what's that guy up to at a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.90,0:16:51.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, we've identified the kidnapper!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.48,0:16:53.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Masashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s childhood friend, Rokuda Takuji.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.61,0:16:57.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a danger that he might flee.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.03,0:16:59.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he refuses to come along voluntarily, arrest him without a warrant
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.24,0:17:00.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.83,0:17:01.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.95,0:17:04.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just now he came flying by with a strange look on his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.91,0:17:06.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Who did?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.50,0:17:11.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ooh, Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.09,0:17:12.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.30,0:17:14.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was him, there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.76,0:17:23.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.31,0:17:25.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you get covered with blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.31,0:17:30.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you went in and fought with the culprit to try to look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.90,0:17:34.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's the kidnapper Rokuda's blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.19,0:17:36.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He saved him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.74,0:17:39.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} broke into the apartment and saved Rokuda.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.16,0:17:43.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.83,0:17:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.63,0:17:58.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.93,0:18:02.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He slit his wrists. The ambulance just left with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.72,0:18:05.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was discovered soon enough, so it looks like he'll survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.02,0:18:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, it seems he's going to come in voluntarily afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.19,0:18:11.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did you know he was trying to commit suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.36,0:18:14.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s socks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.19,0:18:17.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I asked him why his socks were wet,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.78,0:18:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} said when he went back to Rokuda's place there was a stranger in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.78,0:18:30.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From that I figured after Rokuda let Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} go, he took off his disguise and was planning to kill himself in the bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.21,0:18:35.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since his socks were wet, that meant Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} went into the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.42,0:18:37.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he must have been right beside Rokuda,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.71,0:18:42.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Rokuda was still conscious at the time, he should have reacted to Kouta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} being in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.59,0:18:47.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. Rokuda found the lottery tickets that had been returned in his mailbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.06,0:18:53.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He realized Emoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} still cared for him, and was unable to endure the weight of the crime he had committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.73,0:18:57.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how were you so sure that Rokuda Takuji was the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.69,0:19:00.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing that Masashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} sent back and was in his mailbox...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.86,0:19:05.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the only thing who's value could be known beforehand and could be stolen by stealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.78,0:19:07.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It had to be the lottery tickets.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.91,0:19:10.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why didn't you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.21,0:19:11.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.71,0:19:18.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasn't confident about my deduction, and so I wanted to confirm it first. I'm Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.22,0:19:23.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Inspector, I'll leave the rest to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.23,0:19:26.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.10,0:19:30.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.39,0:19:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you write up the detailed report back at headquarters for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.02,0:19:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.35,0:19:36.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.06,0:19:36.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.07,0:19:39.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I need to wait here for the search warrant
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.86,0:19:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can use my car. Have you been drinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.24,0:19:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only had softdrinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.41,0:19:48.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.54,0:19:49.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.62,0:19:51.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't do anything that requires an apology.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.79,0:19:53.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But aren't you angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.08,0:19:55.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Do I look like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.13,0:19:58.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, if it's about the singles party...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.71,0:20:03.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's OK. I bet Chiba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} told you they were short on people and you couldn't refuse, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.80,0:20:08.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess you were looking forward to some girls coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.26,0:20:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're mad about what I just did then?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.60,0:20:16.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Upon reflection, I know I should have shared my conclusions with you, as my superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.94,0:20:20.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But before bknew it, my body was moving on its own and I was running there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.24,0:20:24.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.91,0:20:27.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.24,0:20:31.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What you did was far more important than arresting someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.58,0:20:34.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did a really magnificent thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.50,0:20:39.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm upset that I wasn't thinking about what the suspect would be feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.46,0:20:43.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I'm mad at myself for fixating only on apprehending him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.80,0:20:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when at the same time some other person could see the big picture, I regret that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.01,0:20:52.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no. I only figured it out because I also buy lottery tickets frequently.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.39,0:20:55.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, it's just like the chance you have with lottery.tickets...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.13,0:21:00.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two people who are dating meet at a singles party they were invited to separately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.11,0:21:05.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's true. My tickets are never winners either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.30,0:21:10.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I'm just another losing ticket, I guess?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.74,0:21:13.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no! You're a high-class big win
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.16,0:21:15.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watch where you're going
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.92,0:21:18.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.71,0:21:21.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! I'll swear upon my cherry blossom police badge.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.92,0:21:23.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then will you make certain?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.42,0:21:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I'm a win or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.13,0:21:29.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, gladly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.02,0:21:38.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be you forgot we were back here?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.90,0:23:07.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Another singles party?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.11,0:23:11.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, we're short on people again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.41,0:23:13.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yumi... Sorry but I'm going to pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.62,0:23:16.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've learned'mydesson before.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.99,0:23:20.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? A smorgasbord of cake after dinner, all you can eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.46,0:23:22.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus its all paid by them?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.38,0:23:23.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go, I'll go!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.79,0:23:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll catch the mugger in the third district right away and come running!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.42,0:23:29.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.72,0:23:33.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.47,0:23:40.72,Signs,,0,0,0,,Gum
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.18,0:23:36.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mikami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.52,0:23:40.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! I understand now!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.41,0:23:46.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan - A Strange Child.
